info.description: The Selling Partner API for Direct Fulfillment Shipping provides programmatic access to a direct fulfillment vendor's shipping data.
info.title: Selling Partner API for Direct Fulfillment Shipping

get.description:
Returns a list of shipping labels created during the time frame that you specify. You define that time frame using the createdAfter and createdBefore parameters. You must use both of these parameters. The date range to search must not be more than 7 days.

**Usage Plan:**

| Rate (requests per second) | Burst |
| ---- | ---- |
| 10 | 10 |

The `x-amzn-RateLimit-Limit` response header returns the usage plan rate limits that were applied to the requested operation, when available. The table above indicates the default rate and burst values for this operation. Selling partners whose business demands require higher throughput may see higher rate and burst values then those shown here. For more information, see [Usage Plans and Rate Limits in the Selling Partner API](doc:usage-plans-and-rate-limits-in-the-sp-api).

parameters.name: shipFromPartyId
parameters.description: The vendor warehouseId for order fulfillment. If not specified, the result will contain orders for all warehouses.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The limit to the number of records returned.

parameters.name: createdAfter
parameters.description: Shipping labels that became available after this date and time will be included in the result. Must be in ISO-8601 date/time format.

parameters.name: createdBefore
parameters.description: Shipping labels that became available before this date and time will be included in the result. Must be in ISO-8601 date/time format.

parameters.name: sortOrder
parameters.description: Sort ASC or DESC by order creation date.

x-docgen-enum-table-extension.description: Sort in ascending order by order creation date.
Sort in descending order by order creation date.

parameters.name: nextToken
parameters.description: Used for pagination when there are more ship labels than the specified result size limit. The token value is returned in the previous API call.

itemSequenceNumber.description: Item Sequence Number for the item. This must be the same value as sent in the order for a given item.

buyerProductIdentifier.description: Buyer's Standard Identification Number (ASIN) of an item. Either buyerProductIdentifier or vendorProductIdentifier is required.

pieceNumber.description: The piece number of the item in this container. This is required when the item is split across different containers.

vendorProductIdentifier.description: The vendor selected product identification of the item. Should be the same as was sent in the Purchase Order, like SKU Number.

packedQuantity.description: Total item quantity packed in the container.

address.description: Identification of the party by address.

taxRegistrationDetails.description: Tax registration details of the entity.

shippedDate.description: This field indicates the date of the departure of the shipment from vendor's location. Vendors are requested to send ASNs within 30 minutes of departure from their warehouse/distribution center or at least 6 hours prior to the appointment time at the Amazon destination warehouse, whichever is sooner. Shipped date mentioned in the Shipment Confirmation should not be in the future.

x-docgen-enum-table-extension.description: Orders that have left the warehouse have shipped status.
Status for orders rejected due to quality issues with products on the floor, or the physical and virtual inventory do not match.

isPriorityShipment.description: Provide the priority of the shipment.

vendorOrderNumber.description: The vendor order number is a unique identifier generated by a vendor for their reference.

estimatedDeliveryDate.description: Date on which the shipment is expected to reach the buyer's warehouse. It needs to be an estimate based on the average transit time between the ship-from location and the destination. The exact appointment time will be provided by buyer and is potentially not known when creating the shipment confirmation.

trackingNumber.description: This is required to be provided for every package and should match with the trackingNumber sent for the shipment confirmation.

statusCode.description: Indicates the shipment status code of the package that provides transportation information for Amazon tracking systems and ultimately for the final customer.

reasonCode.description: Provides a reason code for the status of the package that will provide additional information about the transportation status.

statusDateTime.description: The date and time when the shipment status was updated. This field is expected to be in ISO-8601 date/time format, with UTC time zone or UTC offset. For example, 2020-07-16T23:00:00Z or 2020-07-16T23:00:00+01:00.

StatusUpdateDetails.description: Details for the shipment status update given by the vendor for the specific package.

taxRegistrationType.description: Tax registration type for the entity.

taxRegistrationNumber.description: Tax registration number for the party. For example, VAT ID.

taxRegistrationAddress.description: Address associated with the tax registration number.

taxRegistrationMessages.description: Tax registration message that can be used for additional tax related details.

TaxRegistrationDetails.description: Tax registration details of the entity.

name.description: The name of the person, business or institution at that address.

addressLine2.description: Additional street address information, if required.

addressLine3.description: Additional street address information, if required.

city.description: The city where the person, business or institution is located.

county.description: The county where person, business or institution is located.

district.description: The district where person, business or institution is located.

stateOrRegion.description: The state or region where person, business or institution is located.

postalCode.description: The postal code of that address. It contains a series of letters or digits or both, sometimes including spaces or punctuation.

countryCode.description: The two digit country code in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 format.

phone.description: The phone number of the person, business or institution located at that address.

estimatedDeliveryDateTime.description: Date on which the shipment is expected to reach the customer delivery location. This field is expected to be in ISO-8601 date/time format, with UTC time zone or UTC offset. For example, 2020-07-16T23:00:00Z or 2020-07-16T23:00:00+01:00.

apptWindowStartDateTime.description: This field indicates the date and time at the start of the appointment window scheduled to deliver the shipment. apptWindowEndDateTime.description: This field indicates the date and time at the end of the appointment window scheduled to deliver the shipment. unitOfMeasure.description: The unit of measure for dimensions.

Decimal.description:
A decimal number with no loss of precision. Useful when precision loss is unacceptable, as with currencies. Follows RFC7159 for number representation.
**Pattern** : `^-?(0|([1-9]\\d*))(\\.\\d+)?([eE][+-]?\\d+)?$`.

amount.description: Quantity of units shipped for a specific item at a shipment level. If the item is present only in certain packages or pallets within the shipment, please provide this at the appropriate package or pallet level.

unitOfMeasure.description: Unit of measure for the shipped quantity.

packageIdentifier.description: Identifier for the package. The first package will be 001, the second 002, and so on. This number is used as a reference to refer to this package from the pallet level.

trackingNumber.description: Package tracking identifier from the shipping carrier.

shipMethod.description: Ship method to be used for shipping the order. Amazon defines Ship Method Codes indicating shipping carrier and shipment service level. Ship Method Codes are case and format sensitive. The same ship method code should returned on the shipment confirmation. Note that the Ship Method Codes are vendor specific and will be provided to each vendor during the implementation.
